The seminar will aim to look at a diverse group of such practices by emphasizing student research projects on topics which they have already embarked on before the seminar, or on which they wish to begin work in the seminar. Following a beginning segment of the seminar in which readings on historiography and film historiography will be discussed, students will be asked to make presentations concerning their research problematics; they may be able to rent or screen films in connection with their presentations.    *** Those students interested in taking this seminar should email Robert Sklar at rs9@nyu.edu by August 6, 2005. The email should state your status in the grad program, any relevant past courses/reading/research, your particular interest in the seminar, and particular project, if any, that you would like to work on during the seminar. The seminar will aim to look at a diverse group of such practices by emphasizing student research projects on topics which they have already embarked on before the seminar, or on which they wish to begin work in the seminar. Following a beginning segment of the seminar in which readings on historiography and film historiography will be discussed, students will be asked to make presentations concerning their research problematics; they may be able to rent or screen films in connection with their presentations.    *** Those students interested in taking this seminar should email Robert Sklar at rs9@nyu.edu by August 6, 2005. The email should state your status in the grad program, any relevant past courses/reading/research, your particular interest in the seminar, and particular project, if any, that you would like to work on during the seminar.
